  "text": "In the case of specimens proposed to exhibit polarity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , the cells interpreted as micromeres and macromeres are equally well interpreted as belonging to a continuum of cell sizes and their distributions do not provide convincing evidence for cell polarity. In the specimens described as having duet cleavage, there is little difference in size between the proposed macromeres and micromeres and they are hard to distinguish from, for example, the rotational cleavage found in some sponges [45] .",
